Approach:
Create a graph where indices of the words are the vertices of the graph and an edge exists between two vertices if those 2 words differ by a single letter.

Consider below input -
Input: beginWord = "hit", endWord = "cog", wordList = ["hot","dot","dog","lot","log","cog"]

In my code, beginWord has vertex 0 and words in wordList have vertices = (i+1), so for e.g. vertex of "hot" is 1 and that of "cog" is 6.
The graph for this input will look as shown in below image -

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/a40e177c-e89f-4e9a-acd5-3f5f008d06bd_1660473707.6309211.png)


In above graph we can see the vertices and the corresponding words, the src is the beginWord and dest is the endWord. 
Our answer is **all the shortest paths between beginWord and endWord**.
Those two paths are marked by orange and purple crosses in above image.
0 -> 1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 6 i.e. ["hit","hot","dot","dog","cog"]
0 -> 1 -> 4 -> 5 -> 6 i.e. ["hit","hot","lot","log","cog"]


