solutions.content:
This is similar to [127. Word Ladder](https://leetcode.com/problems/word-ladder/discuss/811753/Evolve-from-intuition-to-optimal) but more difficult. I would like to share my thinking process that leads to an easy solution.
1. Normally we use a queue to implement BFS. Since the problem asks for shortest path, we need to visit the nodes level by level. A visited set is usually used to avoid visiting duplicate nodes. The problem is hard due to an implicit requirement: ***we need to consider duplicate nodes at the same level but only expand from distinct nodes when generating the next level***. Ex, both a and b can be transformed to c and they are distinct paths {a->c, b->c}. The visited set can be implemented to not include nodes in the new level and we need another set to dedupe the level. Since we already use a set to store nodes in a level, we no longer need queue. We can just use the set for BFS. If we still use queue, then we have to move nodes from the set to queue which can be avoided.
2. In BFS, we need to 1) check if a node visited  and 2) mark a node visited to avoid searching the same word.
2.1 Check visited nodes
We only add nodes on shortest path to graph. If we add a visited node to graph, then it is not a shortest path and result could be wrong. So we have to check visted nodes before adding it to graph. The only place we can add to graph is when expending a node where we have both the parent and the child. 
2.2 Mark a node visited
When we expand to a node from its parent, we cannot mark the node visited because we need to visit duplicate nodes at the same level. After a level is generated, we mark all node in the level visited before visiting any node. If we generate the next level without marking every node in the previous level visited, we will visit duplicate nodes and that's not the shortest path.
3. The words must be in the dictionary. The idea is same as 2.1. We only add valid word to graph. If we add invalid word to graph, the result could be wrong. Ex, if endWord is not in dictionary but added to grap and it is wrong. So we have to check dictionary before add a node to graph.
* BFS
