solutions.content:
The key point is, instead of using `Queue<String>` for #127 Word Ladder, we use `Queue<List<String>>` here to save all possible pathes until we find the endword, and add all possible pathes to our result.

Steps:
1. Push a list containing only `beginWord` to the queue.
2. While the queue has elements, poll the front element of the queue then get last word from this element as `currWord`.
3. The set of words we get from the helper function `getNextWordSet()` are all the adjacent words to the `currWord`. (We can use a hashmap to save this set of words for currWord to avoid repeated calculations)
4. Foreach each adjacent word, create a new list containing the current path as well as this adjacent word, append into the queue. If we find the `endWord`, add the path to our final result.

Code:

```
    public List<List<String>> findLadders(String beginWord, String endWord, List<String> wordList) {
        List<List<String>> result = new ArrayList<>();
        Queue<List<String>> queue = new LinkedList<>();
        Set<String> wordSet = new HashSet<>(wordList);
        // use a hashmap to save a set of valid adjacent words for a given word to avoid repeated calculations
        Map<String, Set<String>> wordMap = new HashMap<>();
        wordSet.add(beginWord);
        List<String> start = new ArrayList<>();
        start.add(beginWord);
        queue.offer(start);
        boolean foundResult = false;
        while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
            int size = queue.size();
            List<String> usedWords = new ArrayList<>();
            for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
                List<String> currList = queue.poll();
                String currWord = currList.get(currList.size() - 1);
                if (!wordSet.contains(currWord)) continue;
                if (!wordMap.containsKey(currWord)) {
                    Set<String> nextWordSet = getNextWordSet(currWord, wordSet);
                    wordMap.put(currWord, nextWordSet);
                }
                Set<String> nextWordSet = wordMap.get(currWord);
                for (String nextWord: nextWordSet) {
                    List<String> nextList = new ArrayList<>();
                    nextList.addAll(currList);
                    nextList.add(nextWord);
                    if (nextWord.equals(endWord)) {
                        result.add(nextList);
                        foundResult = true;
                    } else {
                        queue.offer(nextList);
                    }
                    usedWords.add(currWord);
                }

            }
            // generated words should be removed from wordSet to prevent cycles
            for (String uw: usedWords) wordSet.remove(uw);
            if (foundResult) break;
        }
        return result;
    }

    // check all variations of a given word and check if it matches any word from wordset, 
    // if it has a match, add that word into result set
    private Set<String> getNextWordSet(String word, Set<String> dict) {
        Set<String> result = new HashSet<>();
        char[] array = word.toCharArray(); 
        for (int i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
            for (char c = 'a'; c <= 'z'; c++) {
                if (array[i] == c) continue;
                char t = array[i];
                array[i] = c;
                String nextWord = String.valueOf(array);
                if (dict.contains(nextWord)) result.add(nextWord);
                array[i] = t;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }    
